line_1: Thy soldiery the pope's well-manag'd pack,
line_2: Were train'd beneath his lash and knew the smack,

line_1: And soon return'd with such a Pack
line_2: Of Bulls and Pardons at his Back,

line_1: Bore his whole substance in a pedlar's pack;
line_2: Dawkins, a dealer once, on burthen'd back

line_1: Twitcher, superior to the venal pack
Their common Loves, a lewd abandon'd Pack,
line_2: The Beadle's Lash still flagrant on their Back;

line_1: The slow-pac'd sluggard hunts the pack.
line_2: Yet faithful to the beaten track

line_1: He takes the field, the master of the pack
line_2: Cries, well done Saint — and claps him on the back.

line_1: He cast off his friends, as a huntsman his pack,
line_2: For he knew when he pleas'd he could whistle them back.

line_1: 'Tis a full feast to all the mongril pack
line_2: To run the rambler down, and bring her back.

line_1: Yet as the Hound may fault'ring quit the pack,
line_2: Snuff the foul scent, and hasten yelping back;
